First, it's not fully vegan,you have to ask for no mayo and cheese.Second, their ( homemade?) patty is one of the worst things I've ever tasted,: it was pure mush, tasteless and had chopped peas and carrots randomly mixed in,served on a wheat bun (vegans eat regular eggless buns guys!) and regular burger toppings.Ended up throwing almost the whole things away since it tasted like nothing and the mush texture.Also, one of the female employees kept taking her making off to blow bubbles by the counter,clearly ignoring COVID-19 per cautions.Hopefully they completely change the vegan burger and make it fully vegan (cheese and all) and start to respect the restrictions.

I couldn’t even leave the place before writing this review. This place is AMAZING! It has truly turned our entire trip around and made coming to this (below) freezing city worth it! I searched high and low for a good spot to get a Chicago style vegan hot dog and this didn’t disappoint. Danny the owner was already welcoming us with a smile as we were walking in. He helped us through the menu and gave us some history on the local food traditions. I probably would’ve liked the place regardless of the food, solely because of Danny’s hospitality, but LET ME TELL YOU...I have never seen my boyfriend devour his meal so fast. He said it was the BEST sandwich he’s EVER eaten. We’re Cuban from Miami and he said he will never enjoy a Cuban again unless it’s dipped like this. 😂 Danny, AMAZING job! We will recommend this place over and over and will be back next time we’re in Chicago! ♥️
